          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/220.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Mix</strong> together the tahini, honey, soy sauce, garlic, lime zest, juice of the whole lime<span class=\"text-danger\">(s)</span> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(2 tbsp)</span> of olive oil to form a dressing</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/220.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/220.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/220.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/220.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/220.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Once</strong> the couscous is ready, take small handfuls of the onion and cucumber and squeeze out the excess liquid</p>\r\n<p>Tip: A lot of water will have been drawn out by the salt so squeeze quite hard</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
